This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image restoration and specifically blind motion deblurring. The use of regularization techniques also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) or information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The numerical scheme used for computation could also place it in the optimization and control (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of state-of-the-art methods and experimental results suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
